ZH: 抗生素是一种用来治疗细菌感染的药物。
EN: Antibiotics are medications used to treat bacterial infections.

ZH: 我们应该明智使用抗生素，避免滥用。
EN: We should use antibiotics wisely and avoid overuse.

ZH: 如果不按医生的建议用抗生素，可能会导致耐药性。
EN: Not following the doctor's advice on antibiotics may lead to resistance.

ZH: 抗生素对病毒感染无效。
EN: Antibiotics are ineffective against viral infections.

ZH: 在抗生素被发明前，很多细菌感染都是致命的。
EN: Before antibiotics were invented, many bacterial infections were fatal.

ZH: 请按时按量服用抗生素。
EN: Please take antibiotics on time and as prescribed.

ZH: 抗生素可以削弱肠道菌群的健康。
EN: Antibiotics can weaken the health of the gut microbiome.

ZH: 对抗生素过敏的人要特别注意。
EN: People allergic to antibiotics should be especially careful.

ZH: 医生会根据病情严重程度来决定是否使用抗生素。
EN: Doctors will decide whether to use antibiotics based on the severity of the condition.

ZH: 抗生素的种类和剂量会因人而异。
EN: The type and dosage of antibiotics vary from person to person.

ZH: 抗生素不适用于治疗传染性疾病。
EN: Antibiotics are not suitable for treating contagious diseases.

ZH: 使用抗生素会对环境造成影响。
EN: The use of antibiotics can have an impact on the environment.

ZH: 抗生素的过度使用可能会导致健康问题。
EN: Overuse of antibiotics may lead to health issues.

ZH: 孕妇应慎重使用抗生素。
EN: Pregnant women should use antibiotics with caution.

ZH: 抗生素的有效性可能随时间而变化。
EN: The effectiveness of antibiotics may change over time.

ZH: 孩子用抗生素时要格外小心。
EN: Children should be extra careful when using antibiotics.

ZH: 抗生素可以预防细菌感染。
EN: Antibiotics can prevent bacterial infections.

ZH: 抗生素应该避免与特定药物一同使用。
EN: Antibiotics should be avoided when used with certain medications.

ZH: 抗生素对耳朵感染有效。
EN: Antibiotics are effective for ear infections.

ZH: 长期使用抗生素可能会对身体产生负面影响。
EN: Long-term use of antibiotics may have negative effects on the body.
